and just screamed for someone to come,

11:22.640 --> 11:24.267
and they all just came in.

11:25.894 --> 11:28.354
They threw me on a gurney, and off I went,

11:28.438 --> 11:29.814
stretcher down the hallway.

11:29.898 --> 11:31.065
I was scared.

11:32.192 --> 11:33.693
I was really thinking about...

11:33.943 --> 11:36.529
"What's gonna happen to my kids
if I don't wake up?"

11:44.704 --> 11:47.624
<i>The old-time medicine man
would sell his snake oil</i>

11:47.707 --> 11:49.334
<i>by positively guaranteeing</i>

11:49.417 --> 11:52.837
<i>it would cure any and every disease
known to man and beast.</i>

11:53.213 --> 11:55.798
<i>Fortunately,
this form of quackery in medicine</i>

11:55.882 --> 11:59.052
<i>is gradually being eliminated
by our food and drug laws,</i>

11:59.135 --> 12:00.845
<i>but there's still another form,</i>

12:00.929 --> 12:03.848
<i>equally dangerous
and far more difficult to control.</i>

12:03.932 --> 12:05.850
<i>Phony machines and devices,</i>

12:05.934 --> 12:10.063
<i>which are supposed to diagnose
and treat disease.</i>

12:10.146 --> 12:11.522
<i>Unlike new drugs,</i>

12:11.606 --> 12:15.526
<i>therapeutic devices do not have to be
proved either safe or effective</i>

12:15.610 --> 12:16.986
<i>before they are sold or used.</i>

12:19.822 --> 12:21.991
The history
of medical devices is odd.

12:22.617 --> 12:28.373
There was an explosion in the 1920s
and '30s and '40s of fraudulent devices

12:28.456 --> 12:31.376
that pretended to put sound waves
into the body to cure cancer

12:31.459 --> 12:34.295
or any number of these weird devices.

12:34.379 --> 12:38.091
Some were dangerous, such as ones
that had radioactive qualities.

12:38.174 --> 12:40.843
<i>There are some as phony
as a three dollar bill.</i>

12:41.344 --> 12:43.972
<i>Like this Zerret Applicator, for example,</i>

12:44.055 --> 12:47.141
<i>which has claimed to cure arthritis
with Z-rays.</i>

12:47.225 --> 12:49.185
<i>There are no Z-rays.</i>

12:50.019 --> 12:53.314
<i>Investigate before you invest
in health services or products.</i>

12:53.398 --> 12:55.275
<i>Help stamp out quackery.</i>

12:55.358 --> 12:57.485
<i>This has been
a public service announcement</i>

12:57.568 --> 12:59.529
<i>from the Food and Drug Administration.</i>

12:59.612 --> 13:02.115
For many years,
devices just came onto the market

13:02.198 --> 13:05.034
with the anecdotes
of doctors who used them,

13:05.118 --> 13:07.120
who would say, "Well, I think it works."

13:07.537 --> 13:12.667
It was only with
the Medical Device Amendments of 1976

13:12.750 --> 13:16.129
that devices came under control of FDA.

13:16.212 --> 13:17.672
At that point, industry argued,

13:17.755 --> 13:21.009
"We don't want to have to test everything
we're already using,

13:21.092 --> 13:22.969
pacemakers and other devices."

13:23.052 --> 13:26.264
And the FDA said,
"Okay, you can grandfather in

13:26.347 --> 13:30.351
anything that was on the market
prior to 1976.

13:31.311 --> 13:34.856
The regulation of medical devices
has always been less than ideal.

13:34.939 --> 13:38.860
Since 1976, the complexity of devices,
the number of devices,

13:38.985 --> 13:41.571
the types of devices,
just rapidly expanded.

13:41.654 --> 13:42.822
So we have the same framework

13:42.905 --> 13:45.491
that was imposed, you know, 40 years ago

13:45.950 --> 13:49.370
for a device world that is much more
complicated today.

13:50.455 --> 13:53.333
<i>Dr. Kessler,
please proceed when ready, sir.</i>

13:53.416 --> 13:58.838
<i>Mr. Chairman, Americans rightfully expect</i>

13:58.921 --> 14:00.715
<i>public health decisions...</i>

14:02.425 --> 14:05.303
<i>to be made in </i> their <i>interest</i>

14:06.012 --> 14:10.308
<i>and to be based on the best science
and medicine.</i>

14:10.683 --> 14:14.354
I was appointed as FDA commissioner
by the first President Bush

14:14.437 --> 14:16.856
and asked to stay on by President Clinton.

14:16.939 --> 14:23.279
FDA is the most important
consumer protection agency in the world.

14:23.821 --> 14:27.408
It regulates virtually everything
that comes in contact with the body.

14:28.326 --> 14:30.620
FDA is organized by centers.

14:30.703 --> 14:32.663
So there's a center for foods.

14:32.747 --> 14:37.043
There's a center for drugs,
there's a center for biologics

14:37.126 --> 14:39.837
and there's a center for medical devices.

14:40.213 --> 14:42.340
And FDA does a credible job

14:42.423 --> 14:45.051
with the vast majority of products.

14:45.134 --> 14:46.719
The problem we have...

14:47.345 --> 14:52.975
is that, when it comes to medical devices,
we built a system that doesn't work.

